Retrieving similarity scores of the protein set

Source: R/requests.R
homology.Rd

Retrieve the protein similarity scores between the input proteins.

homology(identifiers = NULL, species = 9606, caller_identity)

Arguments

identifiers

A character string.
species

A numeric.
caller_identity

A character string.

Source

https://string-db.org/cgi/help.pl?subpage=api

Value

A tibble.

stringId_A

STRING identifier (protein A)

ncbiTaxonId_A

NCBI taxon identifier (protein A)

stringId_B

STRING identifier (protein B)

ncbiTaxonId_B

NCBI taxon identifier (protein B)

bitscore

Smith-Waterman alignment bit score

See also

get_string_ids network interaction_partners homology_best enrichment functional_annotation ppi_enrichment

Other API methods: enrichment, functional_annotation, get_string_ids, homology_best, interaction_partners, network, ppi_enrichment

Examples

# NOT RUN {
# make a homology request
homology(identifiers = c('TP53', 'CDK2'))
# }
